  "texts": [
    "Traditional methods of threat detection face numerous challenges that hinder organizations in maintaining the security of their systems and networks.",
    "The first challenge stems from the ever-evolving and intricate threat landscape.",
    "Cybercriminals are continuously improving their tactics, techniques, and procedures to compromise systems and networks.",
    "This necessitates organizations to constantly update their cybersecurity defenses to stay ahead of emerging threats, such as Ransomware, Phishing attacks, Data Leakage, supply chain compromise, Zeroday exploits, advanced malware, business email compromise, insider threats, and more.",
    "Addressing these threats requires ongoing refinement of threat detection mechanisms, vigilant monitoring, and prompt incident response."
  ],
